The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 21 November is 8,353 (966.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 November, there were 1,114 new confirmed cases (128.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 November, there were 905 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 23% ( 209 extra cases).
